adowFile.Hash` → done ✓\\n\\nBut there's a subtle problem: after commit 1, the committed file has lines 20-24 of agent changes **plus the original content for the rest**. The shadow branch has the **full agent version** (all 200 lines changed). So the hash comparison correctly detects they differ. But what about commit 2?\\n\\nAfter commit 1, `carryForwardToNewShadowBranch` creates a new shadow branch by reading `remainingFiles` from the **working tree** at that moment. So the new shadow branch captures the working tree state after commit 1 — which has the full agent version still in it (the uncommitted hunks). Then commit 2 adds the remaining hunks → `commitFile.Hash == shadowFile.Hash` → carry-forward complete.\\n\\n**This actually works correctly today for `git add -p` scenarios.** The shadow branch acts as a snapshot of \\\"what the agent intended\\\" and each commit is compared against it.\\n\\nSo the real question is: **can we replicate this without a git branch?**\\n\\nThe shadow branch's role in carry-forward is exactly one thing: store the blob hash of each file as the agent wrote it. That's what Option B's `carry_forward_files` map would need — not a SHA-256 of the content, but the **git blob hash** (which is what go-git already computes). After the carry-forward shadow branch is created, it's never appended to — it's only read for hash comparison.\\n\\nSo a revised Option B would store:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"carry_forward\\\": {\\n    \\\"files\\\": {\\n      \\\"src/auth.go\\\": \\\"git:abc123def456...\\\",  // git blob hash from working tree\\n      \\\"src/main.go\\\": \\\"git:789012345678...\\\"\\n    },\\n    \\\"source_checkpoint_id\\\": \\\"a3b2c4d5e6f7\\\"\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThen `filesWithRemainingAgentChanges` would compare the committed file's blob hash against the stored blob hash instead of reading from the shadow tree. Same semantics, no branch needed.\\n\\nThe one thing this **doesn't** handle is `filesOverlapWithContent` in `shouldCondenseWithOverlapCheck` — that function currently reads the actual file content from the shadow tree to compare against the committed content (for the \\\"did the user actually include agent work in this commit\\\" check). For that, we'd need either the blob content or a different heuristic.\\n\\nWant me to look at exactly what `filesOverlapWithContent` needs from the shadow tree to see if we can replace that too, or does this direction feel right so far?\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":815,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":97919,\"output_tokens\":778,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":815,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYkcXdrSvfXKtnpeKxQMR\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"9d40cce2-6c82-4987-9bfb-ea0792d119c6\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-05T21:06:01.788Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"9d40cce2-6c82-4987-9bfb-ea0792d119c6\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"9b854080-5799-41cb-91c1-a3714b4bb75f\",\"version\":\"2.1.69\",\"gitBranch\":\"main\",\"slug\":\"wild-soaring-treasure\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"Stop\",\"hookName\":\"Stop\",\"command\":\"go run ${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks claude-code stop\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"9f1395bd-9ceb-4398-8c24-305957f8ad52\",\"toolUseID\":\"9f1395bd-9ceb-4398-8c24-305957f8ad52\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-05T21:06:01.826Z\",\"uuid\":\"b52911af-f361-48f2-8e67-947e09132249\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"b52911af-f361-48f2-8e67-947e09132249\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"9b854080-5799-41cb-91c1-a3714b4bb75f\",\"version\":\"2.1.69\",\"gitBranch\":\"main\