aude-code stop\",\"durationMs\":965}],\"hookErrors\":[],\"preventedContinuation\":false,\"stopReason\":\"\",\"hasOutput\":false,\"level\":\"suggestion\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-05T21:43:38.732Z\",\"uuid\":\"5b3cbbc9-061c-4bc3-85d8-1a83e5dbe89a\",\"toolUseID\":\"9949eb9b-eed3-4458-951a-f726dfb5b7db\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"5b3cbbc9-061c-4bc3-85d8-1a83e5dbe89a\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"9b854080-5799-41cb-91c1-a3714b4bb75f\",\"version\":\"2.1.69\",\"gitBranch\":\"main\",\"slug\":\"wild-soaring-treasure\",\"type\":\"system\",\"subtype\":\"turn_duration\",\"durationMs\":116023,\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-05T21:43:38.733Z\",\"uuid\":\"25355f53-4974-42ca-ae3f-9ea7514fb143\",\"isMeta\":false}\n{\"type\":\"queue-operation\",\"operation\":\"enqueue\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-05T21:44:41.418Z\",\"sessionId\":\"9b854080-5799-41cb-91c1-a3714b4bb75f\",\"content\":\"<task-notification>\\n<task-id>a6033997951dd0fc7</task-id>\\n<tool-use-id>REDACTED</tool-use-id>\\n<status>completed</status>\\n<summary>Agent \\\"Research diff/hunk libraries in Go\\\" completed</summary>\\n<result>Perfect! Now I have enough information to provide comprehensive research findings. Let me create my summary:\\n\\n## Research Summary: Hunk-Level Diff Computation in Go\\n\\nBased on my thorough exploration of the codebase and available Go libraries, here are my findings:\\n\\n### 1. Go Libraries for Diff Computation\\n\\n#### **go-git v5** (`github.com/go-git/go-git/v5`)\\n- **File-level diffs**: Available via `DiffTree()`, `DiffTreeContext()`, `DiffTreeWithOptions()`\\n  - Location: `plumbing/object/difftree.go`\\n  - Returns `Changes` type (slice of `*Change` objects)\\n  - Each `Change` has `From` and `To` fields (type `ChangeEntry`)\\n  - Supports rename detection via `DiffTreeOptions`\\n\\n- **Hunk-level diffs**: Supported via `Patch()` / `PatchContext()` methods\\n  - Location: `plumbing/object/patch.go`\\n  - `Change.Patch()` → `*Patch` with file patches\\n  - `Changes.Patch()` → `*Patch` with all file patches\\n  - Each `FilePatch` has `Chunks()` returning `[]fdiff.Chunk`\\n  - Each `Chunk` has `Content()` and `Type()` (Operation: Equal/Add/Delete)\\n\\n- **Unified diff generation**: Built-in encoding\\n  - Location: `plumbing/format/diff/unified_encoder.go`\\n  - `UnifiedEncoder.Encode(patch Patch)` generates standard unified diff\\n  - Includes `hunksGenerator` (internal struct) that computes hunk headers (`@@ -start,count +start,count @@`)\\n  - Configurable context lines (default: 3)\\n\\n#### **sergi/go-diff** (`github.com/sergi/go-diff/diffmatchpatch`)\\n- **Low-level line/char diffs**: \\n  - Location: `diffmatchpatch/diff.go`\\n  - `DiffMain(text1, text2 string, checklines bool) []Diff`\\n  - `DiffMainRunes()` for rune-level operations\\n  - Returns `[]Diff` where each `Diff` has `Type` (DiffDelete/DiffInsert/DiffEqual) and `Text`\\n  - Powers go-git's internal diff computation\\n\\n- **Patch object representation**:\\n  - Location: `diffmatchpatch/patch.go`\\n  - `Patch` struct with `Start1/Start2`, `Length1/Length2`, `diffs []Diff`\\n  - `PatchMake()` converts diffs to patches\\n  - `String()` emits GNU diff format (`@@ -start,length +start,length @@`)\\n  - `PatchAddContext()` adds surrounding lines for context\\n\\n#### **gitleaks/go-gitdiff** (`github.com/gitleaks/go-gitdiff/gitdiff`)\\n- **Git unified diff parsing** (does NOT compute diffs, only parses):\\n  - Location: `gitdiff/gitdiff.go`\\n  - `Parse(r io.Reader)` streams parsed file/fragment structure\\n  - Excellent for consuming `git diff` output\\n\\n- **Text fragment representation** (hunks):\\n  - Location: `gitdiff/text.go`\\n  - `TextFragment` struct:\\n    - `OldPosition/OldLines`, `NewPosition/NewLines` (hunk header ranges)\\n    - `LinesAdded/LinesDeleted`, `LeadingContext/TrailingContext`\\n    - `Lines []Line` - individual line ops (OpContext/OpAdd/OpDelete)\\n  - `TextFragment.Header()` returns canonical `@@ -start,count +start,count @@` format\\n  - `TextFragment.Validate()` checks consistency\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 2. Computing \\\"Agent's Diff\\\" (Base → Agent Version)\\n\\n**Recommended approach: Use go-git's tree diff API**\\n\\n```\\ngo-git.object.DiffTree(baseTree *Tree, agentTree *Tree) → Changes\\n→ Changes.Patch() → Patch\\n→ Patch.FilePatches() → []FilePatch\\n→ FilePatch.Chunks() → []Chunk (already has operations and content)\\n```\\n\\n**Implementation path:**\\n1. Get base commit tree from repo\\n2. Build agent's in-memory tree from workspace files (or shadow branch tree if building from metadata)\\n3. Call `DiffTreeWithOptions(ctx, baseTree, agentTree, &DiffTreeOptions{DetectRenames: true})`\\n4. Convert to hunks: iterate `Changes` → call `Patch()` on each → extract hunks from `hunksGenerator` (internal to unified_encoder)\\n\\n**Performance notes:**\\n- File-level diffing is O(N*d) where N = min lines and d = diff size (Myers algorithm via sergi/go-diff)\\n- Tree diffing is incremental - only processes changed files\\n- For 10 files: typically milliseconds on modern hardware\\n- Timeout available via `utils/diff.DoWithTimeout(src, dst, timeout)`\\n\\n**Key types:**\\n- `github.com/go-git/go-git/v5/plumbing/object.Change` - single file change\\n- `github.com/go-git/go-git/v5/plumbing/object.Changes` - collection of changes (sortable)\\n- `github.com/go-git/go-git/v5/plumbing/object.Patch` - unified diff representation\\n- `github.com/go-git/go-git/v5/plumbing/format/diff.FilePatch` - per-file patch\\n- `github.com/go-git/go-git/v5/plumbing/format/diff.Chunk` - diff chunk (Equal/Add/Delete with content)\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 3. Detecting Hunk Consumption (Partial Commits)\\n\\n**Challenge**: Given diff A (base → agent) and diff B (parent → committed), determine which hunks from A are \\\"covered\\\" by B.\\n\\n**Current approach in codebase**: Content-aware overlap detection\\n- Location: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/content_overlap.go`\\n- Uses blob hash comparison for file-level detection\\n- `hasSignificantContentOverlap()` - line-based content matching (not hunk-aware)\\n- Falls back to filename-only checks if metadata unavailable\\n\\n**For hunk-level detection, options:**\\n\\n**Option 1: Three-way merge approach** (NOT directly available in Go)\\n- git internally uses `merge-base` + recursive 3-way merge\\n- No standard Go library implements git's native 3-way merge\\n- `go-git` has `merge_base.go` but only for finding common ancestors, not for merge computation\\n\\n**Option 2: Patch application / reversal** (PRACTICAL)\\n- Use `git apply --reverse --check` to test if a hunk would apply cleanly\\n- Or: convert hunk to unified diff, attempt dry-run application\\n- `gitleaks/go-gitdiff` has `Apply()` function for this:\\n  ```go\\n  gitdiff.Apply(dst io.Writer, src io.ReaderAt, f *File) error\\n  ```\\n- Can use this to test if agent diff applies to committed state\\n\\n**Option 3: Line-by-line context matching** (RELIABLE, PERFORMANT)\\n- Extract hunks from agent diff A\\n- For each hunk: check if context lines exist in parent→committed diff B\\n- If context lines are present in B, hunk was likely incorporated\\n- Account for fuzz factor (git apply uses 1-line fuzz by default)\\n- Build content overlap detection at hunk granularity (similar to current approach, but on hunks)\\n\\n**Option 4: Fuzzy matching** (RECOMMENDED FOR PARTIAL STAGING)\\n- Given agent hunk H with content, search committed file for:\\n  - Exact line match (strict)\\n  - Subsequence match (5+ consecutive lines from H exist in B)\\n  - Content distance (Levenshtein-style similarity threshold)\\n- Current codebase already does this with `hasSignificantContentOverlap()` - could be adapted to hunks\\n\\n**Best approach for split commits scenario:**\\n1. Compute agent diff A using go-git DiffTree + Patch\\n2. Compute parent→committed diff B\\n3. For each hunk in A:\\n   - Extract hunk context lines (leading + trailing context from go-gitdiff parsing)\\n   - Check if these lines appear in B's changed region\\n   - If yes: hunk is \\\"carried forward\\\" to committed\\n   - If no: hunk remains \\\"uncommitted\\\" (needs carry-forward)\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 4. Storing Diffs Efficiently\\n\\n**JSON-serializable hunk representation** (inspired by gitleaks/go-gitdiff):\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"file_path\\\": \\\"src/auth.go\\\",\\n  \\\"old_range\\\": {\\\"start\\\": 42, \\\"count\\\": 15},\\n  \\\"new_range\\\": {\\\"start\\\": 42, \\\"count\\\": 18},\\n  \\\"old_end_context\\\": \\\"@@ function definition\\\",\\n  \\\"leading_context_lines\\\": 3,\\n  \\\"trailing_context_lines\\\": 3,\\n  \\\"lines\\\": [\\n    {\\\"op\\\": \\\"context\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"  existing code\\\"},\\n    {\\\"op\\\": \\\"delete\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"  old_line\\\"},\\n    {\\\"op\\\": \\\"add\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"  new_line\\\"},\\n    {\\\"op\\\": \\\"context\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"  more existing code\\\"}\\n  ],\\n  \\\"stats\\\": {\\\"added\\\": 2, \\\"deleted\\\": 1}\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Size comparison:**\\n- Unified diff (text): ~100-500 bytes per small hunk\\n- Full blob storage: typically 1-10 KB per file\\n- Hunk JSON: ~200-800 bytes per hunk (includes metadata)\\n- **Recommendation**: Store unified diff text (most compact), parse on-demand using gitleaks/go-gitdiff\\n\\n**For session metadata**: Store hunk summary in JSONL format\\n```jsonl\\n{\\\"type\\\": \\\"hunk_summary\\\", \\\"file\\\": \\\"auth.go\\\", \\\"hunks\\\": 3, \\\"added\\\": 42, \\\"deleted\\\": 8, \\\"status\\\": \\\"partial_staged\\\"}\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 5. Handling Line Number Drift After Partial Commits\\n\\n**The problem**: After `git add -p` (partial staging), remaining hunks have shifted line numbers because earlier hunks were applied.\\n\\n**Solutions:**\\n\\n**Option A: Fuzzy Context Matching** (SIMPLE, PRACTICAL)\\n- Don't track absolute line numbers after first commit\\n- Instead, track hunk by its \\\"context signature\\\": leading/trailing context lines + content hash\\n- When re-mapping, search for this signature in the current file\\n- If found within fuzzy distance (fuzz factor = 1-3 lines), apply hunk\\n- This is how `git apply` handles rebased patches\\n\\n**Option B: Dynamic Recomputation** (MOST RELIABLE)\\n- Don't try to re-map hunks after commits\\n- Instead: after partial commit, recompute diffs between HEAD and current agent tree\\n- Remaining uncommitted hunks naturally have correct line numbers\\n- Store \\\"checkpoint ID\\\" + \\\"agent tree hash\\\", not individual hunks\\n- Current codebase already does this via shadow branch storage\\n\\n**Option C: Blob-based Rewind** (CURRENT APPROACH)\\n- Current `filesWithRemainingAgentChanges()` uses file-level comparison\\n- Could be extended to hunk level:\\n  1. Get agent version of file from shadow branch\\n  2. Get committed version from HEAD\\n  3. Get working tree version from disk\\n  4. Recompute hunks: committed ← agent\\n  5. For each hunk: check if it exists in working tree\\n  6. If not in working tree: hunk was discarded (don't carry forward)\\n  7. If in working tree but different lines: apply fuzzy matching\\n\\n**Recommended for this use case**: **Option B + Option C combined**\\n- Use line-number-independent hunk identity (context signature)\\n- When carrying forward after partial commit, recompute diffs on-demand\\n- Don't cache absolute line numbers across commits\\n- Location: Extend `filesWithRemainingAgentChanges()` to return hunks, not just files\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 6. Key Files & Types to Use\\n\\n**For hunk-level diff computation:**\\n```\\ngithub.com/go-git/go-git/v5/plumbing/object:\\n  - DiffTree(a, b *Tree) → Changes\\n  - Changes.Patch() → *Patch\\n  - Patch.FilePatches() → []FilePatch\\n  - FilePatch.Chunks() → []Chunk\\n  - Operation (const: Equal=0, Add=1, Delete=2)\\n\\ngithub.com/go-git/go-git/v5/plumbing/format/diff:\\n  - UnifiedEncoder (for emitting unified diff format)\\n  - FilePatch, Chunk (inte