indings:\\n\\n## Comprehensive Integration Analysis: Hunk-Level Carry-Forward with Entire CLI\\n\\nBased on research and codebase analysis, here's a detailed integration plan for hunk-level carry-forward in the Entire CLI.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## PART 1: Custom Git Refs Research Findings\\n\\n### 1. Go-git Support for Custom Refs\\n\\n**Yes, go-git supports custom refs under arbitrary namespaces:**\\n- `Storer.SetReference()` (plumbing API) accepts any ref name via `plumbing.NewHashReference(refName, hash)`\\n- Reference names can be arbitrary paths like `refs/entire/carry_forward/<session-id>`\\n- Example from `/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/clean_test.go:414-417`:\\n  ```go\\n  shadowRef := plumbing.NewHashReference(plumbing.NewBranchReferenceName(shadowBranchName), commitHash)\\n  if err := repo.Storer.SetReference(shadowRef); err != nil { ... }\\n  ```\\n- The codebase already uses this pattern for shadow branches (`refs/heads/entire/<hash>-<worktreeHash>`)\\n\\n### 2. Push Behavior for Custom Refs\\n\\n**Custom refs under `refs/entire/` are NOT pushed by default with `git push`:**\\n- Standard `git push` only pushes `refs/heads/*` and `refs/tags/*`\\n- Custom refs in `refs/entire/` remain local-only\\n- **To push custom carry-forward refs**, you would need:\\n  - Explicit refspec: `git push origin refs/entire/carry_forward/*:refs/entire/carry_forward/*`\\n  - Or `git push --mirror` (mirrors all refs, but has other implications)\\n  - Or configure: `[remote \\\"origin\\\"] push = +refs/entire/carry_forward/*:refs/entire/carry_forward/*`\\n\\n**Current strategy**: The codebase already keeps carry-forward data local-only via shadow branches on `refs/heads/entire/`, which is the right approach.\\n\\n### 3. Garbage Collection Safety\\n\\n**Custom refs keep objects reachable, same as regular branches:**\\n- Git gc respects all refs (branches, tags, custom refs) as reachability roots\\n- Objects referenced by `refs/entire/carry_forward` are NOT garbage-collected\\n- Custom refs can have gc policies via config: `[gc \\\"refs/entire/*\\\"] reflogExpire = never`\\n- **Recommendation**: Add gc config to preserve carry-forward refs indefinitely\\n\\n### 4. Clone Behavior\\n\\n**Custom refs are NOT fetched by default by `git clone`:**\\n- Only `refs/heads/*` and `refs/tags/*` are fetched by default\\n- Custom refs remain on the origin remote\\n- **For Entire CLI**: This is fine—carry-forward refs are development-time artifacts that don't need to sync across clones\\n\\n### 5. Excluding Refs from Push/Fetch\\n\\n**Negative refspecs with `^` prefix exclude refs:**\\n```bash\\n# Exclude refs/entire/ from push\\ngit push origin refs/heads/*:refs/heads/* ^refs/entire/*:refs/entire/*\\n\\n# Exclude from fetch\\ngit fetch origin refs/heads/*:refs/heads/* ^refs/entire/carry_forward/*\\n```\\n\\n**For Entire CLI**: The CLI should explicitly exclude `refs/entire/` from push operations or require explicit opt-in to push them.\\n\\n### 6. go-git References Iteration\\n\\n**go-git's `repo.References()` can filter by prefix:**\\n```go\\niter, err := repo.References()  // Returns all refs\\niter.ForEach(func(ref *plumbing.Reference) error {\\n  if strings.HasPrefix(ref.Name().String(), \\\"refs/entire/carry_forward/\\\") {\\n    // Process carry-forward refs\\n  }\\n  return nil\\n})\\n```\\n\\nThe codebase already uses this pattern in `/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/temporary.go:184-196` to list shadow branches.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## PART 2: Integration Analysis with Existing Codebase\\n\\n### Architecture Overview\\n\\nThe hunk-level carry-forward would use:\\n- **Storage**: `refs/entire/carry_forward/<session-id>/<commit-hash>` (local-only ref)\\n- **Metadata**: Stored in shadow branch metadata directory or as ref-scoped JSON\\n- **Computation**: Done at checkpoint condensation time (first-commit)\\n- **Application**: At PrepareCommitMsg time (next commit)\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 1. **content_overlap.go** —