rward ref not found: %w\\\", err)\\n  }\\n  \\n  // Parse hunk_state.json from tree\\n  // ...\\n}\\n\\n// UpdateCarryForwardRef updates the ref hash after WriteTemporary\\nfunc (s *State) UpdateCarryForwardRef(refHash plumbing.Hash) {\\n  s.CarryForwardRefHash = refHash.String()\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Design rationale**:\\n- Keep `.json` files small by storing only the ref hash, not full hunk data\\n- Full hunk state lives in git objects (more robust and version-controlled)\\n- This avoids duplicating diff data in both state files and git refs\\n\\n**Lines affected**: Lines 32-158 (State struct definition), new helper methods at end of file\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 5. **manual_commit_condensation.go** — Agent Diff Computation\\n\\n**Current State (lines 96-266)**: `CondenseSession()` condenses shadow branch metadata to permanent storage.\\n\\n**Changes Needed**:\\n\\n#### A. Add method to compute agent diff at first-commit time:\\n\\nNew method after line 266 (after CondenseSession):\\n```go\\n// computeAgentDiffForCondensation calculates the agent's diff from base to shadow branch.\\n// This enables hunk-level carry-forward detection: which hunks were consumed vs. remain.\\nfunc (s *ManualCommitStrategy) computeAgentDiffForCondensation(ctx context.Context, \\n  repo *git.Repository, \\n  baseCommit *object.Commit, \\n  shadowCommit *object.Commit,\\n  filesTouched []string,\\n) (map[string]string, error) {\\n  logCtx := logging.WithComponent(ctx, \\\"attribution\\\")\\n  \\n  baseTree, err := baseCommit.Tree()\\n  if err != nil {\\n    logging.Debug(logCtx, \\\"computeAgentDiffForCondensation: failed to get base tree\\\", slog.String(\\\"error\\\", err.Error()))\\n    return nil, err\\n  }\\n  \\n  shadowTree, err := shadowCommit.Tree()\\n  if err != nil {\\n    logging.Debug(logCtx, \\\"computeAgentDiffForCondensation: failed to get shadow tree\\\", slog.String(\\\"error\\\", err.Error()))\\n    return nil, err\\n  }\\n  \\n  diffs := make(map[string]string)\\n  for _, filePa