rryForwardHunks()` | ~2295-2320 | New method | Fetch hunk state from refs |\\n| `checkpoint/temporary.go` | `WriteTemporary()` | 85-142 | Add hunk logic | Compute and store agent diffs |\\n| `checkpoint/temporary.go` | NEW: `computeAgentDiffs()` | ~145-170 | New method | Parse diffs into hunks |\\n| `checkpoint/temporary.go` | NEW: `buildHunkState()` | ~172-190 | New method | Convert diffs to HunkState |\\n| `session/state.go` | `State` struct | 32-158 | Add fields | CarryForwardRefHash, LastPartialCommitHunks |\\n| `manual_commit_condensation.go` | `CondenseSession()` | 126-129, 233-253 | Update | Compute and store agent diffs |\\n| `manual_commit_condensation.go` | NEW: `computeAgentDiffForCondensation()` | ~270-310 | New method | Agent diff computation |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Custom Ref Namespace Design\\n\\n**Location**: `refs/entire/carry_forward/<session-id>/<base-commit-hash[:7]>`\\n\\n**Contents** (git commit object):\\n```\\nTree:\\n  .entire/\\n    hunk_state.json       # { filename -> [hunks] }\\n  <actual files>          # User files matching filesTouched\\n    \\nCommit message:\\n  Carry-forward: <session-id>\\n  \\n  Entire-Session: <session-id>\\n  Entire-Strategy: manual-commit\\n  Entire-Hunk-Metadata: .entire/hunk_state.json\\n```\\n\\n**Push behavior**: Explicit opt-in only via config or CLI flag (not pushed by default)\\n\\n**GC behavior**: Add config to preserve:\\n```\\n[gc \\\"refs/entire/*\\\"]\\n  reflogExpire = never\\n```\\n\\n**Lifecycle**:\\n1. Created after first commit in session (by `carryForwardToNewShadowBranch`)\\n2. Updated with each partial commit\\n3. Deleted when session ends and all files are committed\\n4. Cleaned up by `gc` after 30+ days if session orphaned\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Performance Considerations\\n\\n- **Hunk parsing overhead**: ~30-50ms per session (profile before optimizing)\\n- **Cache parsed hunks** in session state for re-use across multiple commits\\n- **Lazy-load** hunk data only when `filesWithRemainingAgentChanges