ent modifies files during a session, users may commit those changes across\\nmultiple `git commit` invocations (split commits). The system needs to track which\\nparts of the agent's work have been committed and which remain, so that:\\n\\n1. Each commit gets its own checkpoint with accurate metadata\\n2. The system knows when all agent work has been committed (carry-forward complete)\\n3. No git refs (shadow branches) need to linger after the session ends\\n\\n### Current Behavior (File-Level)\\n\\nToday, carry-forward operates at **file granularity**:\\n\\n- Agent modifies files A, B, C\\n- User commits A, B → carry-forward tracks file C\\n- User commits C → carry-forward complete\\n\\nFor partial commits (`git add -p`), the system detects \\\"file still has changes\\\" via\\nwhole-file blob hash comparison + working tree dirty check, but doesn't know WHICH\\nhunks were committed. The shadow branch must persist for the entire carry-forward\\nperiod to hold the agent's file blobs for comparison.\\n\\n### Desired Behavior (Hunk-Level)\\n\\nThe system should track agent changes at the **hunk/diff level**:\\n\\n- Agent modifies `auth.go` (lines 20-24 and lines 100-120)\\n- User commits lines 20-24 via `git add -p` → system knows lines 100-120 remain\\n- User commits lines 100-120 → carry-forward complete for this file\\n- Accurate per-commit attribution: commit 1 gets credit for lines 20-24, commit 2 for 100-120\\n- Shadow branch deleted after first commit; carry-forward uses lightweight local ref\\n\\n## Design\\n\\n### Algorithm: Three-Way Diff (diff3)\\n\\nThe core algorithm uses **three-way diffing** to classify every chunk of a file:\\n\\nGiven three versions:\\n- **O** (origin/base) — file state before the agent (`state.AttributionBaseCommit`)\\n- **A** (agent) — what the agent wrote (blob stored in carry-forward ref)\\n- **B** (committed) — what the user committed (in HEAD tree)\\n\\ndiff3 classifies each region:\\n\\n| O→A | O→B | Classification | Action |\\n|-----|-----|---------------|--------|\\n| unchanged | unchanged | Untouched | Skip |\\n| **changed** | unchanged | Agent change NOT committed | **Remaining** — keep in carry-forward |\\n| unchanged | **changed** | User's own edit | Skip — not from agent |\\n| **same change** | **same change** | Agent change committed | **Consumed** — remove from carry-forward |\\n| **different changes** | **different changes** | Agent change modified by user | **Consumed** (user took ownership) |\\n\\nThis naturally handles:\\n- **Partial staging** (`git add -p`): consumed hunks show as \\\"same change in both\\\"\\n- **User edits between commits**: user-only regions classified correctly\\n- **Reverts**: if user reverts an agent hunk, O→B shows unchanged → \\\"remaining\\\" is cleared\\n- **User modifications of agent work**: both-changed-differently → consumed (user took ownership)\\n\\n#### Why diff3 over alternatives\\n\\n| Approach | Pros | Cons |\\n|----------|------|------|\\n| **diff3 (chosen)** | Exact classification, handles all edge cases, proven algorithm | Needs all 3 versions available |\\n| Patch commutation (git-absorb) | Elegant, well-founded in theory | Only detects overlap, not consumption direction |\\n| Reverse-apply check | Simple concept | Fragile with context changes, requires shelling out |\\n| Hunk line-range overlap | Fast | Breaks with line drift, can't handle user edits |\\n\\n### Storage: `refs/entire/carry_forward`\\n\\nA single custom git ref holds all carry-forward data across all sessions:\\n\\n```\\nrefs/entire/carry_forward → commit → tree:\\n  <session-id-1>/\\n    src/auth.go          ← agent's file blob (version A)\\n    src/main.go\\n  <session-id-2>/\\n    lib/utils.py\\n```\\n\\n**Properties:**\\n- **Not pushed**: Custom refs outside `refs/heads/` and `refs/tags/` are not pushed\\n  by default. The pre-push hook that pushes `entire/checkpoints/v1` ignores it.\\n- **Not fetched**: Not included in default clone/fetch refspecs.\\n- **Prevents GC**: Git treats all refs as reachability roots. Blobs referenced by\\n  this tree are protected from garbage collection.\\n- **Invisible**: Not shown by `git branch` or `git tag`.\\n- **Single ref**: One ref for all sessions. Adding/removing sessions mutates the tree.\\n  When the last session completes, the ref is deleted entirely.\\n- **go-git compatible**: `Storer.SetReference()` accepts arbitrary ref names. The\\n  codebase already uses this pattern for shadow branches.\\n\\n#### Why not other storage options\\n\\n| Option | Problem |\\n|--------|---------|\\n| Shadow branch (`refs/heads/entire/...`) | Visible in `git branch`, one ref per session |\\n| `entire/checkpoints/v1` tree | Pushed to remote, creates unnecessary commits |\\n| Session state JSON | Can't hold git blob references (GC-unsafe) |\\n| Filesystem (`.entire/snapshots/`) | No dedup, no GC integration, uses disk space |\\n\\n### Session State Additions\\n\\nThe session state file (`.git/entire-sessions/<id>.json`) gets minimal new fields:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"carry_forward_base\\\": \\\"abc123def456...\\\",\\n  \\\"carry_forward_files\\\": [\\\"src/auth.go\\\", \\\"src/main.go\\\"]\\n}\\n```\\n\\n- `carry_forward_base`: The base commit hash (O in the diff3 triple). This is the\\n  commit the agent's changes were relative to. Needed to retrieve version O.\\n- `carry_forward_files`: Which files still have remaining agent hunks. Used for quick\\n  checks without reading the carry-forward ref tree.\\n\\nThe actual agent file blobs (version A) live in the carry-forward ref, not in the\\nstate file. The state file only has lightweight metadata.\\n\\n### Lifecycle\\n\\n```\\n                    ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐\\n                    │              ACTIVE SESSION                  │\\n                    │                                             │\\n                    │  Shadow branch: entire/<hash>-<worktree>    │\\n                    │  Stores: file snapshots + transcript        │\\n                    │  (unchanged from today)                     │\\n                    └──────────────────┬──────────────────────────┘\\n                                       │\\n                              First commit\\n                                       │\\n                    ┌──────────────────▼──────────────────────────┐\\n                    │            CONDENSATION                      │\\n                    │                                             │\\n                    │  1. Condense transcript → checkpoints/v1    │\\n                    │  2. Compute remaining files (as today)      │\\n                    │  3. If remaining files:                     │\\n                    │     a. Write agent blobs to carry-forward   │\\n                    │        ref under <session-id>/              │\\n                    │     b. Set carry_forward_base in state      │\\n                    │  4. Delete shadow branch                    │\\n                    └──────────────────┬──────────────────────────┘\\n                                       │\\n                           ┌───────────┴───────────┐\\n                           │                       │\\n                    No remaining files      Has remaining files\\n                           │                       │\\n                    ┌──────▼──────┐    ┌───────────▼──────────────┐\\n                    │  DONE       │    │    CARRY-FORWARD          │\\n                    │  FullyCond. │    │                           │\\n                    │  = true     │    │  On each subsequent       │\\n                    └─────────────┘    │  commit (PostCommit):     │\\n                                       │                           │\\n                                       │  1. For each file in      │\\n                                       │     carry_forward_files:  │\\n                                       │     a. Get O from base    │\\n                                       │     b. Get A from ref     │\\n                                       │     c. Get B from HEAD    │\\n                                       │     d. Run diff3(O, A, B) │\\n                                       │     e. If no \\\"remaining\\\"  │\\n                                       │        chunks → consumed  │\\n                                       │  2. Update ref tree       │\\n                                       │     (remove consumed)     │\\n                                       │  3. Update state file     │\\n                                       │  4. If all consumed →     │\\n                                       │     delete ref subtree,   │\\n                                       │     FullyCondensed=true   │\\n                                       └──────────────────────────┘\\n```\\n\\n### Detailed Flow: PostCommit with Hunk-Level Carry-Forward\\n\\nFor each session in `postCommitProcessSession`:\\n\\n1. **Check carry-forward state**: If `carry_forward_files` is empty, skip (no\\n   carry-forward). Fall through to existing file-level logic for active sessions.\\n\\n2. **Load the three versions** for each carry-forward file:\\n   - **O** (base): `repo.CommitObject(carry_forward_base).Tree().File(path)`\\n   - **A** (agent): read from `refs/entire/carry_forward` tree at `<session-id>/<path>`\\n   - **B** (committed): `HEAD.Tree().File(path)` (the just-committed version)\\n\\n3. **Run diff3** per file:\\n   - Use `epiclabs-io/diff3` or equivalent Go library\\n   - Classify each chunk as consumed, remaining, or user-only\\n\\n4. **Determine file status**:\\n   - If no \\\"remaining\\\" chunks → file is fully consumed\\n   - If \\\"remaining\\\" chunks exist → file stays in carry-forward\\n   - If file was deleted in B → consumed (user removed it, agent work is moot)\\n   - If file not in committed files set → skip (not part of this commit)\\n\\n5. **Update carry-forward ref**:\\n   - Remove consumed files from the `<session-id>/` subtree\\n   - Write a new commit on the ref with the updated tree\\n   - If subtree is empty, remove the session's directory entirely\\n\\n6. **Update session state**:\\n   - Update `carry_forward_files` to only remaining files\\n   - If empty → set `FullyCondensed = true`, clean up ref subtree\\n\\n7. **For checkpoint metadata**: The consumed hunks can be recorded in the checkpoint\\n   on `entire/checkpoints/v1` for per-commit attribution.\\n\\n### Detailed Flow: PrepareCommitMsg with Hunk-Level Carry-Forward\\n\\nFor sessions with `carry_forward_files`:\\n\\n1. **Check staged files overlap**: Intersect staged files with `carry_forward_files`\\n2. **For overlapping files, run diff3** with staged content (from git index) as B:\\n   - If any chunks classify as \\\"consumed\\\" → agent work is being committed → add trailer\\n   - If no consumed chunks → staged content is user-only or reverted → skip trailer\\n3. This replaces the current `stagedFilesOverlapWithContent` for carry-forward sessions\\n\\n### Edge Cases\\n\\n#### User rebases between split commits\\n- `carry_forward_base` points to a commit that may no longer be in the branch history\\n- But the commit object still exists in the repo (not GC'd — still reachable via reflog)\\n- diff3 still works: O is read from the old base commit's tree, A from carry-forward ref\\n- If the base commit IS GC'd (unlikely within 90-day reflog window): fall back to\\n  file-level comparison\\n\\n#### User amends the first commit\\n- PostCommit fires again for the amend\\n- diff3 runs with the amended commit as B\\n- If amend included more agent hunks → those are now consumed\\n- carry_forward_base doesn't change (still the original pre-agent base)\\n\\n#### Agent session resumes (ENDED → ACTIVE via new TurnStart)\\n- `ActionClearEndedAt` already clears `FullyCondensed`\\n- New SaveStep creates a new shadow branch (normal active session flow)\\n- On next commit, fresh condensation + carry-forward computation\\n- Any leftover carry-forward ref data from the previous ended session is overwritten\\n\\n#### Binary files\\n- diff3 doesn't work on binary files\\n- Fall back to file-level blob hash comparison (current behavior)\\n- Detection: check if file content contains null bytes or use go-git's `IsBinary()`\\n\\n#### File renamed between commits\\n- If user renames a carry-forward file, the old path won't match\\n- Detection: use go-git's `DiffTreeWithOptions` with `DetectRenames: true`\\n- If rename detected, update the path in carry-forward ref and state\\n\\n## Go Libraries\\n\\n| Library | Purpose | Notes |\\n|---------|---------|-------|\\n| `epiclabs-io/diff3` | Three-way merge/diff | Go port, returns classified chunks |\\n| `github.com/sergi/go-diff` | Low-level Myers diff | Already a go-git dependency |\\n| `github.com/bluekeyes/go-gitdiff` | Parse unified diff output | Structured `TextFragment` (hunk) types |\\n| `go-git/go-git/v5` | Git operations, tree diff | `DiffTree()` → `Patch()` → `Chunks()` |\\n\\n## Performance Budget\\n\\n| Operation | Expected Time | Notes |\\n|-----------|--------------|-------|\\n| Read 3 file versions from git | 1-3ms | go-git blob reads |\\n| diff3 per file | 2-10ms | Depends on file size |\\n| 5 carry-forward files | 15-65ms total | Parallelizable |\\n| Update carry-forward ref | 5-10ms | Single tree mutation + commit |\\n| **Total PostCommit overhead** | **20-75ms** | Within <200ms budget |\\n\\nCurrent PostCommit is <100ms. Adding hunk tracking stays within 200ms for typical cases.\\n\\n## Migration Path\\n\\n1. **Phase 1**: Implement `refs/entire/carry_forward` storage alongside existing shadow\\n   branch carry-forward. Both paths active. New path used when carry-forward ref exists,\\n   old path as fallback.\\n\\n2. **Phase 2**: At condensation time, always write to carry-forward ref instead of\\n   creating a new shadow branch. Shadow branch deleted immediately after first commit.\\n\\n3. **Phase 3**: Remove shadow-branch carry-forward code. Add diff3-based hunk\\n   consumption detection. File-level comparison becomes the fallback for binary files\\n   and error cases.\\n\\n## Files to Modify\\n\\n| File | Change |\\n|------|--------|\\n| `strategy/content_overlap.go` | Add `hunksWithRemainingAgentChanges()` using diff3 |\\n| `strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` | PostCommit: add carry-forward ref read/write; PrepareCommitMsg: diff3-based overlap |\\n| `strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` | Replace `carryForwardToNewShadowBranch` with `carryForwardToRef` |\\n| `session/state.go` | Add `CarryForwardBase`, `CarryForwardFiles` fields |\\n| `strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go` | At condensation: write agent blobs to carry-forward ref |\\n| `checkpoint/` (new file) | `carry_forward.go`: ref management (read/write/update/cleanup) |\\n| `strategy/cleanup.go` | Add carry-forward ref cleanup to `ListOrphanedItems` |\\n\\n## Open Questions\\n\\n1. Should we store the unified diff text alongside the blob in the carry-forward ref\\n   (for debugging/inspection), or just the blob?\\n2. Should carry-forward ref commits have meaningful messages (for `git log refs/entire/carry_forward`)?\\n3. What's the right stale timeout for carry-forward data? (Currently 7 days for session state)\\n4. Should `entire status` show carry-forward hunk counts per file?\\n\",\"structuredPatch\":[{\"oldStart\":1,\"oldLines\":6,\"newStart\":1,\"newLines\":6,\"lines\":[\" # Hunk-Level Carry-Forward Tracking\",\" \",\"-## Status: Research / Spec\",\"+## Status: Design\",\" \",\" ## Problem Statement\",\" \"]},{\"oldStart\":17,\"oldLines\":165,\"newStart\":17,\"newLines\":290,\"lines\":[\" Today, carry-forward operates at **file granularity**:\",\" \",\" - Agent modifies files A, B, C\",\"-- User commits A, B → carry-forward tracks C\",\"+- User commits A, B → carry-forward tracks file C\",\" - User commits C → carry-forward complete\",\" \",\" For partial commits (`git add -p`), the system detects \\\"file still has changes\\\" via\",\"-blob hash comparison + working tree check, but doesn't know WHICH hunks were committed.\",\"+whole-file blob hash comparison + working tree dirty check, but doesn't know WHICH\",\"+hunks were committed. The shadow branch must persist for the entire carry-forward\",\"+period to hold the agent's file blobs for comparison.\",\" \",\" ### Desired Behavior (Hunk-Level)\",\" \",\" The system should track agent changes at the **hunk/diff level**:\",\" \",\" - Agent modifies `auth.go` (lines 20-24 and lines 100-120)\",\"-- User commits lines 20-24 via `git add -p` → carry-forward knows lines 100-120 remain\",\"+- User commits lines 20-24 via `git add -p` → system knows lines 100-120 remain\",\" - User commits lines 100-120 → carry-forward complete for this file\",\" - Accurate per-commit attribution: commit 1 gets credit for lines 20-24, commit 2 for 100-120\",\"+- Shadow branch deleted after first commit; carry-forward uses lightweight local ref\",\" \",\"-## Requirements\",\"+## Design\",\" \",\"-### Must Have\",\"+### Algorithm: Three-Way Diff (diff3)\",\" \",\"-1. **Track agent's diff, not just file blobs**: Store the actual changes (hunks) the\",\"-   agent made relative to a base commit, not just the resulting file content.\",\"+The core algorithm uses **three-way diffing** to classify every chunk of a file:\",\" \",\"-2. **Detect partial consumption**: When a commit includes some but not all hunks from\",\"-   the agent's diff, correctly identify which hunks remain.\",\"+Given three versions:\",\"+- **O** (origin/base) — file state before the agent (`state.AttributionBaseCommit`)\",\"+- **A** (agent) — what the agent wrote (blob stored in carry-forward ref)\",\"+- **B** (committed) — what the user committed (in HEAD tree)\",\" \",\"-3. **Survive across commits**: The tracking state must persist across multiple commits\",\"-   without requiring a shadow branch. The carry-forward data should be stored in a way\",\"-   that prevents GC of any referenced git objects.\",\"+diff3 classifies each region:\",\" \",\"-4. **Handle user edits between commits**: If the user modifies the file between split\",\"-   commits (adding their own changes alongside the agent's), the system should still\",\"-   correctly identify which agent hunks remain.\",\"+| O→A | O→B | Classification | Action |\",\"+|-----|-----|---------------|--------|\",\"+| unchanged | unchanged | Untouched | Skip |\",\"+| **changed** | unchanged | Agent change NOT committed | **Remaining** — keep in carry-forward |\",\"+| unchanged | **changed** | User's own edit | Skip — not from agent |\",\"+| **same change** | **same change** | Agent change committed | **Consumed** — remove from carry-forward |\",\"+| **different changes** | **different changes** | Agent change modified by user | **Consumed** (user took ownership) |\",\" \",\"-5. **Handle rebases/merges**: If the user rebases between split commits, line numbers\",\"-   shift. The system should handle this gracefully (at minimum: detect and fall back\",\"-   to file-level; ideally: re-map hunks to new positions).\",\"+This naturally handles:\",\"+- **Partial staging** (`git add -p`): consumed hunks show as \\\"same change in both\\\"\",\"+- **User edits between commits**: user-only regions classified correctly\",\"+- **Reverts**: if user reverts an agent hunk, O→B shows unchanged → \\\"remaining\\\" is cleared\",\"+- **User modifications of agent work**: both-changed-differently → consumed (user took ownership)\",\" \",\"-6. **No remote pollution**: Carry-forward state must be local-only. It should not be\",\"-   pushed to remotes.\",\"+#### Why diff3 over alternatives\",\" \",\"-7. **Natural cleanup**: When all hunks are consumed (or the session is stale), the\",\"-   carry-forward state should be cleanable without manual intervention.\",\"+| Approach | Pros | Cons |\",\"+|----------|------|------|\",\"+| **diff3 (chosen)** | Exact classification, handles all edge cases, proven algorithm | Needs all 3 versions available |\",\"+| Patch commutation (git-absorb) | Elegant, well-founded in theory | Only detects overlap, not consumption direction |\",\"+| Reverse-apply check | Simple concept | Fragile with context changes, requires shelling out |\",\"+| Hunk line-range overlap | Fast | Breaks with line drift, can't handle user edits |\",\" \",\"-### Nice to Have\",\"+### Storage: `refs/entire/carry_forward`\",\" \",\"-8. **Per-commit attribution**: Each checkpoint knows exactly which hunks/lines from\",\"-   the agent's diff were included in that specific commit.\",\"+A single custom git ref holds all carry-forward data across all sessions:\",\" \",\"-9. **Revert detection**: If the user reverts specific agent hunks (via `git checkout -p`\",\"-   or manual editing), detect that those hunks are no longer pending rather than\",\"-   keeping them in carry-forward forever.\",\"+```\",\"+refs/entire/carry_forward → commit → tree:\",\"+  <session-id-1>/\",\"+    src/auth.go          ← agent's file blob (version A)\",\"+    src/main.go\",\"+  <session-id-2>/\",\"+    lib/utils.py\",\"+```\",\" \",\"-10. **Efficient storage**: Diffs are typically much smaller than full file blobs.\",\"-    Storing diffs instead of file snapshots could reduce storage overhead.\",\"+**Properties:**\",\"+- **Not pushed**: Custom refs outside `refs/heads/` and `refs/tags/` are not pushed\",\"+  by default. The pre-push hook that pushes `entire/checkpoints/v1` ignores it.\",\"+- **Not fetched**: Not included in default clone/fetch refspecs.\",\"+- **Prevents GC**: Git treats all refs as reachability roots. Blobs referenced by\",\"+  this tree are protected from garbage collection.\",\"+- **Invisible**: Not shown by `git branch` or `git tag`.\",\"+- **Single ref**: One ref for all sessions. Adding/removing sessions mutates the tree.\",\"+  When the last session completes, the ref is deleted entirely.\",\"+- **go-git compatible**: `Storer.SetReference()` accepts arbitrary ref names. The\",\"+  codebase already uses this pattern for shadow branches.\",\" \",\"-## Constraints\",\"+#### Why not other storage options\",\" \",\"-- Must work with go-git v5 (the project's git library)\",\"-- Must work with the existing `entire/checkpoints/v1` metadata branch\",\"-- Must integrate with the existing session state machine (phases: ACTIVE, IDLE, ENDED)\",\"-- Must not slow down git hooks noticeably (prepare-commit-msg, post-commit run on every commit)\",\"-- Must handle binary files gracefully (fall back to file-level for non-text files)\",\"+| Option | Problem |\",\"+|--------|---------|\",\"+| Shadow branch (`refs/heads/entire/...`) | Visible in `git branch`, one ref per session |\",\"+| `entire/checkpoints/v1` tree | Pushed to remote, creates unnecessary commits |\",\"+| Session state JSON | Can't hold git blob references (GC-unsafe) |\",\"+| Filesystem (`.entire/snapshots/`) | No dedup, no GC integration, uses disk space |\",\" \",\"-## Key Design Questions\",\"+### Session State Additions\",\" \",\"-### Q1: How to represent the agent's diff?\",\"+The session state file (`.git/entire-sessions/<id>.json`) gets minimal new fields:\",\" \",\"-Options to explore:\",\"-- **Unified diff format**: Store `diff(base, agent_version)` as a patch. Standard format,\",\"-  tools exist for parsing/applying. But patches are fragile against context changes.\",\"-- **Hunk list with content**: Store each hunk as `{file, start_line, end_line, content}`.\",\"-  More structured, easier to match against commits.\",\"-- **Git tree diff**: Store base_commit + agent_tree_hash, let git compute the diff on\",\"-  demand. Requires keeping both objects reachable.\",\"-- **Line-level hashes**: For each file, store a map of `line_number → hash(line_content)`.\",\"-  Match against committed content by finding which line hashes appear.\",\"+```json\",\"+{\",\"+  \\\"carry_forward_base\\\": \\\"abc123def456...\\\",\",\"+  \\\"carry_forward_files\\\": [\\\"src/auth.go\\\", \\\"src/main.go\\\"]\",\"+}\",\"+```\",\" \",\"-### Q2: How to detect which hunks a commit consumed?\",\"+- `carry_forward_base`: The base commit hash (O in the diff3 triple). This is the\",\"+  commit the agent's changes were relative to. Needed to retrieve version O.\",\"+- `carry_forward_files`: Which files still have remaining agent hunks. Used for quick\",\"+  checks without reading the carry-forward ref tree.\",\" \",\"-Given the agent's diff and a new commit, determine which hunks were included:\",\"-- **Diff intersection**: Compute `diff(parent, commit)` and `diff(base, agent_version)`,\",\"-  find overlapping regions.\",\"-- **Three-way comparison**: Compare base, agent_version, and committed_version to\",\"-  determine which changes came from the agent vs the user.\",\"-- **Patch application**: Apply remaining agent hunks to the committed version; if a hunk\",\"-  applies cleanly, it wasn't consumed; if it fails (already applied), it was consumed.\",\"-- **Content matching**: Check if the committed file contains the lines from each agent\",\"-  hunk at approximately the right position.\",\"+The actual agent file blobs (version A) live in the carry-forward ref, not in the\",\"+state file. The state file only has lightweight metadata.\",\" \",\"-### Q3: Where to store carry-forward state?\",\"+### Lifecycle\",\" \",\"-Options:\",\"-- **`refs/entire/carry_forward`**: Single custom git ref, tree organized by session.\",\"-  Keeps git objects reachable. Not pushed. Not shown in `git branch`.\",\"-- **Session state file** (`.git/entire-sessions/<id>.json`): Store diff data directly\",\"-  in the session state. Simple but potentially large for big diffs.\",\"-- **Hybrid**: Store lightweight references (hashes, line ranges) in session state,\",\"-  keep actual diff content in a git object referenced by a custom ref.\",\"+```\",\"+                    ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐\",\"+                    │              ACTIVE SESSION                  │\",\"+                    │                                             │\",\"+                    │  Shadow branch: entire/<hash>-<worktree>    │\",\"+                    │  Stores: file snapshots + transcript        │\",\"+                    │  (unchanged from today)                     │\",\"+                    └──────────────────┬──────────────────────────┘\",\"+                                       │\",\"+                              First commit\",\"+                                       │\",\"+                    ┌──────────────────▼──────────────────────────┐\",\"+                    │            CONDENSATION                      │\",\"+                    │                                             │\",\"+                    │  1. Condense transcript → checkpoints/v1    │\",\"+                    │  2. Compute remaining files (as today)      │\",\"+                    │  3. If remaining files:                     │\",\"+                    │     a. Write agent blobs to carry-forward   │\",\"+                    │        ref under <session-id>/              │\",\"+                    │     b. Set carry_forward_base in state      │\",\"+                    │  4. Delete shadow branch                    │\",\"+                    └──────────────────┬──────────────────────────┘\",\"+                                       │\",\"+                           ┌───────────┴───────────┐\",\"+                           │                       │\",\"+                    No remaining files      Has remaining files\",\"+                           │                       │\",\"+                    ┌──────▼──────┐    ┌───────────▼──────────────┐\",\"+                    │  DONE       │    │    CARRY-FORWARD          │\",\"+                    │  FullyCond. │    │                           │\",\"+                    │  = true     │    │  On each subsequent       │\",\"+                    └─────────────┘    │  commit (PostCommit):     │\",\"+                                       │                           │\",\"+                                       │  1. For each file in      │\",\"+                                       │     carry_forward_files:  │\",\"+                                       │     a. Get O from base    │\",\"+                                       │     b. Get A from ref     │\",\"+                                       │     c. Get B from HEAD    │\",\"+                                       │     d. Run diff3(O, A, B) │\",\"+                                       │     e. If no \\\"remaining\\\"  │\",\"+                                       │        chunks → consumed  │\",\"+                                       │  2. Update ref tree       │\",\"+                                       │     (remove consumed)     │\",\"+                                       │  3. Update state file     │\",\"+                                       │  4. If all consumed →     │\",\"+                                       │     delete ref subtree,   │\",\"+                                       │     FullyCondensed=true   │\",\"+                                       └──────────────────────────┘\",\"+```\",\" \",\"-### Q4: How to handle line number drift?\",\"+### Detailed Flow: PostCommit with Hunk-Level Carry-Forward\",\" \",\"-Between split commits, line numbers shift because:\",\"-- The first commit may change line counts in the same file\",\"-- The user may add/remove lines in other parts of the file\",\"-- Rebase can rewrite the entire file\",\"+For each session in `postCommitProcessSession`:\",\" \",\"-Options:\",\"-- **Re-diff on each commit**: Recompute `diff(new_base, agent_version)` fresh each time.\",\"-  Requires keeping the agent's intended file content (blob) reachable.\",\"-- **Fuzzy hunk matching**: Match hunks by content rather than line numbers (similar to\",\"-  `git apply --3way`).\",\"-- **Anchor-based tracking**: Identify hunks by surrounding context lines rather than\",\"-  absolute positions.\",\"+1. **Check carry-forward state**: If `carry_forward_files` is empty, skip (no\",\"+   carry-forward). Fall through to existing file-level logic for active sessions.\",\" \",\"-### Q5: How does this interact with the shadow branch during active sessions?\",\"+2. **Load the three versions** for each carry-forward file:\",\"+   - **O** (base): `repo.CommitObject(carry_forward_base).Tree().File(path)`\",\"+   - **A** (agent): read from `refs/entire/carry_forward` tree at `<session-id>/<path>`\",\"+   - **B** (committed): `HEAD.Tree().File(path)` (the just-committed version)\",\" \",\"-The shadow branch is still needed during active sessions (before any commit) for\",\"-`SaveStep`. The hunk-level tracking only kicks in at carry-forward time (after the\",\"-first commit). So the flow would be:\",\"+3. **Run diff3** per file:\",\"+   - Use `epiclabs-io/diff3` or equivalent Go library\",\"+   - Classify each chunk as consumed, remaining, or user-only\",\" \",\"-1. **Active session**: Shadow branch as today (stores full file snapshots + transcript)\",\"-2. **First commit**: Condense to `entire/checkpoints/v1`. Compute and store agent diff.\",\"-   Delete shadow branch.\",\"-3. **Carry-forward**: Use stored diff + custom ref for hunk tracking. No shadow branch.\",\"-4. **Subsequent commits**: Detect consumed hunks, update carry-forward state.\",\"-5. **All hunks consumed**: Clean up carry-forward state. Session fully condensed.\",\"+4. **Determine file status**:\",\"+   - If no \\\"remaining\\\" chunks → file is fully consumed\",\"+   - If \\\"remaining\\\" chunks exist → file stays in carry-forward\",\"+   - If file was deleted in B → consumed (user removed it, agent work is moot)\",\"+   - If file not in committed files set → skip (not part of this commit)\",\" \",\"-## Research Tasks\",\"+5. **Update carry-forward ref**:\",\"+   - Remove consumed files from the `<session-id>/` subtree\",\"+   - Write a new commit on the ref with the updated tree\",\"+   - If subtree is empty, remove the session's directory entirely\",\" \",\"-The following questions need implementation research:\",\"+6. **Update session state**:\",\"+   - Update `carry_forward_files` to only remaining files\",\"+   - If empty → set `FullyCondensed = true`, clean up ref subtree\",\" \",\"-### Research A: Diff computation and storage in Go\",\"+7. **For checkpoint metadata**: The consumed hunks can be recorded in the checkpoint\",\"+   on `entire/checkpoints/v1` for per-commit attribution.\",\" \",\"-- What Go libraries exist for computing unified diffs / working with hunks?\",\"-- Can go-git compute tree-level or file-level diffs efficiently?\",\"-- What's the performance of diff computation in the context of a git hook?\",\"-- How to represent a diff compactly in JSON (for session state) vs as a git object?\",\"+### Detailed Flow: PrepareCommitMsg with Hunk-Level Carry-Forward\",\" \",\"-### Research B: Hunk consumption detection\",\"+For sessions with `carry_forward_files`:\",\" \",\"-- Given an agent diff (base → agent) and a commit diff (parent → commit), what\",\"-  algorithms exist to determine which agent hunks were \\\"consumed\\\" by the commit?\",\"-- How does `git apply --check` work internally? Can we reuse that logic?\",\"-- How does `git rerere` track resolved conflicts? Any applicable patterns?\",\"-- What about three-way merge algorithms — can they tell us \\\"which side contributed\",\"-  which hunk\\\"?\",\"+1. **Check staged files overlap**: Intersect staged files with `carry_forward_files`\",\"+2. **For overlapping files, run diff3** with staged content (from git index) as B:\",\"+   - If any chunks classify as \\\"consumed\\\" → agent work is being committed → add trailer\",\"+   - If no consumed chunks → staged content is user-only or reverted → skip trailer\",\"+3. This replaces the current `stagedFilesOverlapWithContent` for carry-forward sessions\",\" \",\"-### Research C: Existing art in git ecosystem\",\"+### Edge Cases\",\" \",\"-- How do tools like `git absorb` (automatically fixup commits) match hunks to commits?\",\"-- How does `git range-diff` track hunks across rebased commit ranges?\",\"-- How do code review tools (Gerrit, GitHub) track \\\"which comments are outdated\\\" after\",\"-  force-pushes? (Similar problem: mapping hunks across versions.)\",\"-- Are there other tools that solve the \\\"track partial consumption of a diff\\\" problem?\",\"+#### User rebases between split commits\",\"+- `carry_forward_base` points to a commit that may no longer be in the branch history\",\"+- But the commit object still exists in the repo (not GC'd — still reachable via reflog)\",\"+- diff3 still works: O is read from the old base commit's tree, A from carry-forward ref\",\"+- If the base commit IS GC'd (unlikely within 90-day reflog window): fall back to\",\"+  file-level comparison\",\" \",\"-### Research D: Integration with current codebase\",\"+#### User amends the first commit\",\"+- PostCommit fires again for the amend\",\"+- diff3 runs with the amended commit as B\",\"+- If amend included more agent hunks → those are now consumed\",\"+- carry_forward_base doesn't change (still the original pre-agent base)\",\" \",\"-- How would hunk-level tracking integrate with `filesWithRemainingAgentChanges`?\",\"-- What changes to `content_overlap.go` would be needed?\",\"-- How would the `refs/entire/carry_forward` ref be managed (created, updated, cleaned)?\",\"-- What's the migration path from file-level to hunk-level (backward compat)?\",\"-- Impact on hook performance (prepare-commit-msg and post-commit timing)?\",\"+#### Agent session resumes (ENDED → ACTIVE via new TurnStart)\",\"+- `ActionClearEndedAt` already clears `FullyCondensed`\",\"+- New SaveStep creates a new shadow branch (normal active session flow)\",\"+- On next commit, fresh condensation + carry-forward computation\",\"+- Any leftover carry-forward ref data from the previous ended session is overwritten\",\"+\",\"+#### Binary files\",\"+- diff3 doesn't work on binary files\",\"+- Fall back to file-level blob hash comparison (current behavior)\",\"+- Detection: check if file content contains null bytes or use go-git's `IsBinary()`\",\"+\",\"+#### File renamed between commits\",\"+- If user renames a carry-forward file, the old path won't match\",\"+- Detection: use go-git's `DiffTreeWithOptions` with `DetectRenames: true`\",\"+- If rename detected, update the path in carry-forward ref and state\",\"+\",\"+## Go Libraries\",\"+\",\"+| Library | Purpose | Notes |\",\"+|---------|---------|-------|\",\"+| `epiclabs-io/diff3` | Three-way merge/diff | Go port, returns classified chunks |\",\"+| `github.com/sergi/go-diff` | Low-level Myers diff | Already a go-git dependency |\",\"+| `github.com/bluekeyes/go-gitdiff` | Parse unified diff output | Structured `TextFragment` (hunk) types |\",\"+| `go-git/go-git/v5` | Git operations, tree diff | `DiffTree()` → `Patch()` → `Chunks()` |\",\"+\",\"+## Performance Budget\",\"+\",\"+| Operation | Expected Time | Notes |\",\"+|-----------|--------------|-------|\",\"+| Read 3 file versions from git | 1-3ms | go-git blob reads |\",\"+| diff3 per file | 2-10ms | Depends on file size |\",\"+| 5 carry-forward files | 15-65ms total | Parallelizable |\",\"+| Update carry-forward ref | 5-10ms | Single tree mutation + commit |\",\"+| **Total PostCommit overhead** | **20-75ms** | Within <200ms budget |\",\"+\",\"+Current PostCommit is <100ms. Adding hunk tracking stays within 200ms for typical cases.\",\"+\",\"+## Migration Path\",\"+\",\"+1. **Phase 1**: Implement `refs/entire/carry_forward` storage alongside existing shadow\",\"+   branch carry-forward. Both paths active. New path used when carry-forward ref exists,\",\"+   old path as fallback.\",\"+\",\"+2. **Phase 2**: At condensation time, always write to carry-forward ref instead of\",\"+   creating a new shadow branch. Shadow branch deleted immediately after first commit.\",\"+\",\"+3. **Phase 3**: Remove shadow-branch carry-forward code. Add diff3-based hunk\",\"+   consumption detection. File-level comparison becomes the fallback for binary files\",\"+   and error cases.\",\"+\",\"+## Files to Modify\",\"+\",\"+| File | Change |\",\"+|------|--------|\",\"+| `strategy/content_overlap.go` | Add `hunksWithRemainingAgentChanges()` using diff3 |\",\"+| `strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` | PostCommit: add carry-forward ref read/write; PrepareCommitMsg: diff3-based overlap |\",\"+| `strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` | Replace `carryForwardToNewShadowBranch` with `carryForwardToRef` |\",\"+| `session/state.go` | Add `CarryForwardBase`, `CarryForwardFiles` fields |\",\"+| `strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go` | At condensation: write agent blobs to carry-forward ref |\",\"+| `checkpoint/` (new file) | `carry_forward.go`: ref management (read/write/update/cleanup) |\",\"+| `strategy/cleanup.go` | Add carry-forward ref cleanup to `ListOrphanedItems` |\",\"+\",\"+## Open Questions\",\"+\",\"+1. Should we store the unified diff text alongside the blob in the carry-forward ref\",\"+   (for debugging/inspection), or just the blob?\",\"+2. Should carry-forward ref commits have meaningful messages (for `git log refs/entire/carry_forward`)?\",\"+3. What's the right stale timeout for carry-forward data? (Currently 7 days for session state)\",\"+4. Should `entire status` show carry-forward hunk counts per file?\"]}],\"originalFile\":\"# Hunk-Level Carry-Forward Tracking\\n\\n## Status: Research / Spec\\n\\n## Problem Statement\\n\\nWhen an agent modifies files during a session, users may commit those changes across\\nmultiple `git commit` invocations (split commits). The system needs to track which\\nparts of the agent's work have been committed and which remain, so that:\\n\\n1. Each commit gets its own checkpoint with accurate metadata\\n2. The system knows when all agent work has been committed (carry-forward complete)\\n3. No git refs (shadow branches) need to linger after the session ends\\n\\n### Current Behavior (File-Level)\\n\\nToday, carry-forward operates at **file granularity**:\\n\\n- Agent modifies files A, B, C\\n- User commits A, B → carry-forward tracks C\\n- User commits C → carry-forward complete\\n\\nFor partial commits (`git add -p`), the system detects \\\"file still has changes\\\" via\\nblob hash comparison + working tree check, but doesn't know WHICH hunks were committed.\\n\\n### Desired Behavior (Hunk-Level)\\n\\nThe system should track agent changes at the **hunk/diff level**:\\n\\n- Agent modifies `auth.go` (lines 20-24 and lines 100-120)\\n- User commits lines 20-24 via `git add -p` → carry-forward knows lines 100-120 remain\\n- User commits lines 100-120 → carry-forward complete for this file\\n- Accurate per-commit attribution: commit 1 gets credit for lines 20-24, commit 2 for 100-120\\n\\n## Requirements\\n\\n### Must Have\\n\\n1. **Track agent's diff, not just file blobs**: Store the actual changes (hunks) the\\n   agent made relative to a base commit, not just the resulting file content.\\n\\n2. **Detect partial consumption**: When a commit includes some but not all hunks from\\n   the agent's diff, correctly identify which hunks remain.\\n\\n3. **Survive across commits**: The tracking state must persist across multiple commits\\n   without requiring a shadow branch. The carry-forward data should be stored in a way\\n   that prevents GC of any referenced git objects.\\n\\n4. **Handle user edits between commits**: If the user modifies the file between split\\n   commits (adding their own changes alongside the agent's), the system should still\\n   correctly identify which agent hunks remain.\\n\\n5. **Handle rebases/merges**: If the user rebases between split commits, line numbers\\n   shift. The system should handle this gracefully (at minimum: detect and fall back\\n   to file-level; ideally: re-map hunks to new positions).\\n\\n6. **No remote pollution**: Carry-forward state must be local-only. It should not be\\n   pushed to remotes.\\n\\n7. **Natural cleanup**: When all hunks are consumed (or the session is stale), the\\n   carry-forward state should be cleanable without manual intervention.\\n\\n### Nice to Have\\n\\n8. **Per-commit attribution**: Each checkpoint knows exactly which hunks/lines from\\n   the agent's diff were included in that specific commit.\\n\\n9. **Revert detection**: If the user reverts specific agent hunks (via `git checkout -p`\\n   or manual editing), detect that those hunks are no longer pending rather than\\n   keeping them in carry-forward forever.\\n\\n10. **Efficient storage**: Diffs are typically much smaller than full file blobs.\\n    Storing diffs instead of file snapshots could reduce storage overhead.\\n\\n## Constraints\\n\\n- Must work with go-git v5 (the project's git library)\\n- Must work with the existing `entire/checkpoints/v1` metadata branch\\n- Must integrate with the existing session state machine (phases: ACTIVE, IDLE, ENDED)\\n- Must not slow down git hooks noticeably (prepare-commit-msg, post-commit run on every commit)\\n- Must handle binary files gracefully (fall back to file-level for non-text files)\\n\\n## Key Design Questions\\n\\n### Q1: How to represent the agent's diff?\\n\\nOptions to explore:\\n- **Unified diff format**: Store `diff(base, agent_version)` as a patch. Standard format,\\n  tools exist for parsing/applying. But patches are fragile against context changes.\\n- **Hunk list with content**: Store each hunk as `{file, start_line, end_line, content}`.\\n  More structured, easier to match against commits.\\n- **Git tree diff**: Store base_commit + agent_tree_hash, let git compute the diff on\\n  demand. Requires keeping both objects reachable.\\n- **Line-level hashes**: For each file, store a map of `line_number → hash(line_content)`.\\n  Match against committed content by finding which line hashes appear.\\n\\n### Q2: How to detect which hunks a commit consumed?\\n\\nGiven the agent's diff and a new commit, determine which hunks were included:\\n- **Diff intersection**: Compute `diff(parent, commit)` and `diff(base, agent_version)`,\\n  find overlapping regions.\\n- **Three-way comparison**: Compare base, agent_version, and committed_version to\\n  determine which changes came from the agent vs the user.\\n- **Patch application**: Apply remaining agent hunks to the committed version; if a hunk\\n  applies cleanly, it wasn't consumed; if it fails (already applied), it was consumed.\\n- **Content matching**: Check if the committed file contains the lines from each agent\\n  hunk at approximately the right position.\\n\\n### Q3: Where to store carry-forward state?\\n\\nOptions:\\n- **`refs/entire/carry_forward`**: Single custom git ref, tree organized by session.\\n  Keeps git objects reachable. Not pushed. Not shown in `git branch`.\\n- **Session state file** (`.git/entire-sessions/<id>.json`): Store diff data directly\\n  in the session state. Simple but potentially large for big diffs.\\n- **Hybrid**: Store lightweight references (hashes, line ranges) in session state,\\n  keep actual diff content in a git object referenced by a custom ref.\\n\\n### Q4: How to handle line number drift?\\n\\nBetween split commits, line numbers shift because:\\n- The first commit may change line counts in the same file\\n- The user may add/remove lines in other parts of the file\\n- Rebase can rewrite the entire file\\n\\nOptions:\\n- **Re-diff on each commit**: Recompute `diff(new_base, agent_version)` fresh each time.\\n  Requires keeping the agent's intended file content (blob) reachable.\\n- **Fuzzy hunk matching**: Match hunks by content rather than line numbers (similar to\\n  `git apply --3way`).\\n- **Anchor-based tracking**: Identify hunks by surrounding context lines rather than\\n  absolute positions.\\n\\n### Q5: How does this interact with the shadow branch during active sessions?\\n\\nThe shadow branch is still needed during active sessions (before any commit) for\\n`SaveStep`. The hunk-level tracking only kicks in at carry-forward time (after the\\nfirst commit). So the flow would be:\\n\\n1. **Active session**: Shadow branch as today (stores full file snapshots + transcript)\\n2. **First commit**: Condense to `entire/checkpoints/v1`. Compute and store agent diff.\\n   Delete shadow branch.\\n3. **Carry-forward**: Use stored diff + custom ref for hunk tracking. No shadow branch.\\n4. **Subsequent commits**: Detect consumed hunks, update carry-forward state.\\n5. **All hunks consumed**: Clean up carry-forward state. Session fully condensed.\\n\\n## Research Tasks\\n\\nThe following questions need implementation research:\\n\\n### Research A: Diff computation and storage in Go\\n\\n- What Go libraries exist for computing unified diffs / working with hunks?\\n- Can go-git compute tree-level or file-level diffs efficiently?\\n- What's the performance of diff computation in the context of a git hook?\\n- How to represent a diff compactly in JSON (for session state) vs as a git object?\\n\\n### Research B: Hunk consumption detection\\n\\n- Given an agent diff (base → agent) and a commit diff (parent → commit), what\\n  algorithms exist to determine which agent hunks were \\\"consumed\\\" by the commit?\\n- How does `git apply --check` work internally? Can we reuse that logic?\\n- How does `git rerere` track resolved conflicts? Any applicable patterns?\\n- What about three-way merge algorithms — can they tell us \\\"which side contributed\\n  which hunk\\\"?\\n\\n### Research C: Existing art in git ecosystem\\n\\n- How do tools like `git absorb` (automatically fixup commits) match hunks to commits?\\n- How does `git range-diff` track hunks across rebased commit ranges?\\n- How do code review tools (Gerrit, GitHub) track \\\"which comments are outdated\\\" after\\n  force-pushes? (Similar problem: mapping hunks across versions.)\\n- Are there other tools that solve the \\\"track partial consumption of a diff\\\" problem?\\n\\n### Research D: Integration with current codebase\\n\\n- How would hunk-level tracking integrate with `filesWithRemainingAgentChanges`?\\n- What changes to `content_overlap.go` would be needed?\\n- How would the `refs/entire/carry_forward` ref be managed (created, updated, cleaned)?\\n- What's the migration path from file-level to hunk-level (backward compat)?\\n- Impact on hook performance (prepare-commit-msg and post-commit timing)?\\n\"},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"3feeecb1-b366-4bd7-9669-918ff7cd8c4c\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"6501786c-d5ff-41fb-8350-03ceff988955\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"9b854080-5799-41cb-91c1-a3714b4bb75f\",\"version\":\"2.1.69\",\"gitBranch\":\"main\",\"slug\":\"wild-soaring-treasure\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01VJp9Uwc3mdPoFLBW5ChfxT\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Spec is updated at `docs/architecture/hunk-level-carry-forward.md`. Here's the summary:\\n\\n**Core design:**\\n- **diff3** for hunk consumption detection — classifies every chunk as consumed/remaining/user-only using three versions (base, agent, committed)\\n- **`refs/entire/carry_forward`** as a single local-only ref holding agent file blobs, organized by session ID\\n- Shadow branch lifetime shrinks to \\\"session start → first commit\\\" — no more lingering refs\\n- Minimal session state additions: just `carry_forward_base` (commit hash) and `carry_forward_files` (file list)\\n\\n**Key decisions from research:**\\n- diff3 is the right algorithm (not patch commutation or reverse-apply)\\n- `epiclabs-io/diff3` exists as a Go library\\n- go-git supports custom refs natively\\n- Performance fits within hook budget (~20-75ms for typical carry-forward)\\n\\n**Migration is incremental** — three phases from \\\"both paths active\\\" to \\\"shadow branch carry-forward removed.\\\"\\n\\nThe open questions at the bottom are things to decide before implementation. Want to discuss any of those, or does the overall direction look right?\"}],\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":4034,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":144847,\"output_tokens\":276,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":4034,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYkfx8Lj2Ca4542q1yNy1\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"91b1b57a-a14b-4a13-b210-33e509373391\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-05T21:50:40.983Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"91b1b57a-a14b-4a13-b210-33e509373391\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"9b854080-5799-41cb-91c1-a3714b4bb75f\",\"version\":\"2.1.69\",\"gitBranch\":\"main\",\"slug\":\"wild-soaring-treasure\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"Stop\",\"hookName\":\"Stop\",\"command\":\"go run ${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks claude-code stop\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"6a91566b-8e8a-48be-ad78-2b7ac587ca21\",\"toolUseID\":\"6a91566b-8e8a-48be-ad78-2b7ac587ca21\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-05T21:50:41.021Z\",\"uuid\":\"8315efcb-f42d-47b7-bacf-8823871b4fa0\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"8315efcb-f42d-47b7-bacf-8823871b4fa0\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"9b854080-5799-41cb-91c1-a3714b4bb75f\",\"version\":\"2.1.69\",\"gitBranch\":\"main\",\"slug\":\"wild-soaring-treasure\",\"type\":\"system\",\"subtype\":\"stop_hook_summary\",\"hookCount\":1,\"hookInfos\":[{\"command\":\"go run ${CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks claude-code stop\",\"durationMs\":1014}],\"hookErrors\":[],\"preventedContinuation\":false,\"stopReason\":\"\",\"hasOutput\":false,\"level\":\"suggestion\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-05T21:50:42.035Z\",\"uuid\":\"d